[[Turkmenistan]] had a total primary energy supply ([[TPES]]) of 26.75 [[tonne of oil equivalent|Mtoe]] in 2014.<ref name=iea2014 /> Electricity consumption was 14.64 [[TWh]]. 
Most of this primary energy came from fossil fuels.<ref name="iea2014">{{cite web|title=IEA - Report|url=http://www.iea.org/statistics/statisticssearch/report/?product=Indicators&country=TURKMENIST|website=www.iea.org|accessdate=5 November 2016}}</ref>
All of the electricity is generated with natural gas.

