'''Forged composite''' is a technology that uses [[Carbon fiber reinforced polymer|carbon fiber composite material]] and was developed jointly between [[Lamborghini]] and [[Callaway Golf Company]] who introduced it in their [[Sesto Elemento]] [[concept car]] and [[Diablo Octane]] [[Wood (golf)|driver]]s, respectively. The application of this technology was originally developed at the [http://www.lambolab.org Automobili Lamborghini Advanced Composite Structures Laboratory (ACSL)] in Seattle, WA,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://compositesmanufacturingmagazine.com/2012/01/structure-sport-style/|title=Structure, Sport and Style {{!}} Composites Manufacturing Magazine|date=2012-01-01|newspaper=Composites Manufacturing Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2016-10-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.compositesworld.com/articles/sixth-element-lamborghini-accelerates-cfrp|title=Sixth Element: Lamborghini accelerates CFRP|last=|first=|date=|website=www.compositesworld.com|publisher=|access-date=2016-10-10}}</ref> where the Lamborghini-Callaway partnership was initially formed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://blog.caranddriver.com/lamborghini-and-callaway-golf-partner-on-carbon-fiber-research-create-forged-composite/|title=Paris 2010: Lamborghini and Callaway Golf Partner On Carbon-Fiber Research, Create “Forged Composite”|access-date=2016-10-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.autoblog.com/2010/10/04/driving-force-lamborghini-and-callaway-golf-collaborate-on-new/|title=Driving Force: Lamborghini and Callaway Golf collaborate on new forms of carbon fiber|last=Joseph|first=Noah|website=Autoblog|access-date=2016-10-10}}</ref> This partnership, along with forged composite technology, was announced at the 2010 [[Paris Motor Show]] when Lamborghini unveiled its concept car.<ref name="2PASLFC">{{cite web|url=http://www.autoevolution.com/news/2010-paris-auto-show-lamborghini-forged-composite-24969.html|title=2010 Paris Auto Show: Lamborghini Forged Composite|date=2010-10-01|publisher=SoftNews NET|accessdate=2010-11-15|work=autoevolution|author=Dumitrache, Alina}}</ref> The United States [[trademark]] for forged composite was filed on July 13, 2010, in the category Toys and Sporting Goods Products.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trademarkia.com/forged-composite-85083657.html|title=Forged Composite|publisher=Trademarkia.com|accessdate=2010-11-15}}</ref>  

Forged Composite is not a specific material, but an encompassing technology which combines the material, preform definition, molding and curing processes, and specific design features to create a forged composite carbon fiber part.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://read.nxtbook.com/wiley/plasticsengineering/september2015/fromspe_supercarsinseattle.html|title=Plastics Engineering - September 2015 - Supercars in Seattle|access-date=2016-10-10}}</ref>  The material which is used in Forged Composite technology is an evolution of [[CFSMC|carbon fiber sheet molding compounds]] (CFSMC) with improved fibers, higher fiber volume content, and an improved molding process; all of which increase the average strength values and reduce variability over standard carbon fiber SMC.<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Feraboli|first=P.|last2=Gasco|first2=F.|date=2011|title=Lamborghini "Forged Composite" Technology for the Suspension Arms of the Sesto Elemento|url=http://www.lambolab.org/wp-content/uploads/03research/pub/05chop/2011-ASC-montreal-forged-suspens-ICE.pdf|journal=American Society of Composites 26th Technical Conference Proceedings (Montreal, Quebec, Canada)|volume=}}</ref>  The material is one-third as dense as metal [[titanium]] but stronger,<ref name="DtBLIaLM">{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748703848204575608621726607004|title=Drive the Ball Like It's a Lamborghini, Maybe: Not Your Father's Persimmon: Callaway's Latest Assault on the Tee Box Is a New Material Called 'Forged Composite'|date=2010-11-13|accessdate=2010-11-15|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|author=Newport, John Paul}}</ref> and consists of chopped [[Carbon fibers|carbon fiber]] [[Tow|tows]] that are sandwiched between two layers of filmed [[resin]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.caranddriver.com/features/forged-composite-tech-department|title=The Next Frontier in Carbon Fiber: Forged Composite - Tech Dept.|access-date=2016-10-10}}</ref>  It uses about 500,000 intertwined [[turbostratic]] fibers per square inch.<ref name=2PASLFC/>  The structure of the high strength carbon fibers is described as turbostratic, that is the fibers contain intertwined and folded sheets of carbon atoms aligned with the length of the fiber, and the intertwining improved the fiber strength. The result, which is superior to predecessor alloys used in the automotive and golf industries, is significantly improved load carrying capacity as measured in bending per unit of mass.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://shop.callawaygolf.com/forged-composite/forged-composite,default,sc.html|title=Introducing Forged Composite|publisher=[[Callaway Golf Company]]|accessdate=2010-11-15}}</ref>  Due to its chopped nature, it can be molded into much more complex geometries than traditional carbon fiber composites, and is suitable to make three-dimensional parts and parts which feature complex details such as thickness transitions, holes, compound curvature, etc.  Chopped carbon fiber materials produced by [http://quantumcomposites.com/pages/home/news.php Quantum Composites Inc.] of Bay City, MI, as well as [[Mitsubishi Rayon]] of Toyohashi, Japan, can be used for Forged Composite technology.

Lamborghini originally used Forged Composite technology on both the inner [[monocoque]] and the [[Double wishbone suspension|wishbone suspension]] arms of the Sesto Elemento.<ref name=":0" />  Since then, Lamborghini has used Forged Composite for the interior trim and seats of the 2012 [[Aventador j|Aventador J]], 2012 [[Lamborghini Urus|Urus concept]], 2013 [[Lamborghini Veneno|Veneno]], and the 2014 Veneno Roadster.  The 2015 [[Lamborghini Huracán|Huracan]] features a Forged Composite engine bay cover and optional interior trim package which won the JEC Composites Innovation Award for Automotive Interiors in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.volkswagenag.com/en/news/2016/3/Lamborghini.html|title=Volkswagen Group Lamborghini Wins the Innovation Award at the JEC Composites 2016|last=Group|first=Volkswagen|website=www.volkswagenag.com|access-date=2016-10-10}}</ref>  In June 2016, the world's first carbon fiber [[Connecting rod|connecting rods]], made using Forged Composite technology, were unveiled at the Lamborghini ACSL facility in Seattle.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://blog.caranddriver.com/lamborghini-is-forging-ahead-with-forged-carbon-fiber-we-visit-their-u-s-based-lab|title=Lamborghini Is Forging Ahead with Forged Carbon Fiber; We Visit Their U.S.-Based Lab|access-date=2016-10-10}}</ref>  [http://www.unionbindingcompany.com Union Binding Company] entered a partnership with the Lamborghini ACSL in order to develop a [[Snowboard#Bindings|snowboard binding]] using Forged Composite technology.  In 2014, the all-Forged Composite "Union FC" snowboard binding was launched and subsequently won the 2014 ISPO Product of the Year Award.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://snowboarding.transworld.net/news/union-forged-fc-binding-lands-ispo-product-year/|title=Union Forged FC Binding Lands ISPO Product Of The Year {{!}} TransWorld SNOWboarding|date=2014-01-27|newspaper=TransWorld SNOWboarding|language=en-US|access-date=2016-10-10}}</ref>

This technology marks the first collaborative product of the ongoing Callaway and Lamborghini alliance to combine research and development efforts towards their mutual goal of power-to-weight ratio and weight reduction.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.golfnewsnow.ca/2010/10/07/forged-composite-on-leading-edge-of-callaway-lamborghini-collaboration/|title=Forged Composite On Leading Edge Of Callaway / Lamborghini Collaboration|work=[[Golf News Now]]|accessdate=2010-11-15|date=2010-10-07}}</ref> The effect of the improvement is that the Callaway Diablo Octane drivers average about {{convert|8|yd|0}} greater distance per [[Golf stroke mechanics#List of shots|drive]] than their predecessor Diablo Edge drivers and the Sesto Elemento, with its Forged Composite [[chassis]], is one-third lighter than the Lamborghini [[Superleggera]] and goes from zero to {{convert|60|mph|abbr=on}} almost a full second faster.<ref name="DtBLIaLM" />

