[[File:Gloppedalsura by Nevestv 20170423 P2.jpg|thumb|300 px|Gloppedalsura]] '''Gloppedalsura''', or '''Gloppura''', is a [[scree]] in Gloppedalen, [[Rogaland]], Norway, in the [[Gjesdal]] and [[Bjerkreim]] municipalities. It is one of the largest screes in Scandinavia and Northern Europe.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Gloppura |first=Geir |last=Thorsnæs |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor-last=Bolstad | editor-first=Erik | editor-link= |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=https://snl.no/Gloppura |language=Norwegian |accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref><ref name=naf2010>{{cite book |title=[[NAF Veibok]] 2010&ndash;2012 |edition=29 |publisher=Norges Automobil-Forbund |editor=Evensen, Knut Harald |location=Oslo |language=Norwegian |page=240 |year=2010}}</ref>
==World War 2== During the invasion of Norway, 250 Norwegian soldiers used the scree as a natural fortress and held back two German battalions. One Norwegian soldier lost his life in the battle. Losses on the German side are uncertain and varies between 12 and 44 soldiers.
